COMPONENT NAME: JKM MSSQL Simple
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Journalizing Knowledge Module - This JKM provides simple journalizing procedures on Microsoft SQLServer tables - The following objects are created: - Subscribers central table - Journal table - Triggers on the journalized table that tracks the data changes in the Journal table - Views for selecting data
Restrictions: - This Knowledge Module creates triggers on your source tables. Be sure to validate the scalability of your applications before releasing your developments in your production systems.

<? package com.oracle.odi.km.ext; public class translator { public static String translate( String colType ) throws Exception { // Is source column a uniqueidentifier? if ( colType.toUpperCase().equals( "UNIQUEIDENTIFIER") ) { return( "(36)" ); } else { return ("");} }; } ?>
from java.util import Date as date import time, os import java.sql as sql import java.lang as lang
import java.io as jio
class JMMMsSql:
def __init__(self,con): self.repodriver = con[0] self.repourl = con[1] self.repouser = con[2] self.repopass = con[3] self.repoworkschema= con[4] if self.repoworkschema=='' : repoworkschema=None self.repodataschema = con[5] if self.repodataschema=='' : repodataschema=None lang.Class.forName(self.repodriver) self.repoCx = sql.DriverManager.getConnection(self.repourl, self.repouser, self.repopass) self.repoCx.setCatalog(self.repoworkschema) self.stmt = self.repoCx.createStatement() # Use Target Work Database
# Create JV$ view self.requete = """ create view <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_WORK_SCHEMA")%>.<%=odiRef.getInfo( "JRN_VIEW")%> as select case when (<%=odiRef.getColList("", "convert(varchar<?=translator.translate(\u0022[SOURCE_DT]\u0022)?>,TARG.[COL_NAME])", " + ", "", "PK")%>) is null then 'D' else 'I' end <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_FLAG, JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN.JRN_DATE <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "JRN.[COL_NAME]\t\t" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "PK")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "TARG.[COL_NAME]\t\t" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "NOT PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN left outer join <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> TARG on ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "JRN.[COL_NAME]\t= TARG.[COL_NAME]", "\nand\t", "", "PK")%> ) where JRN.JRN_DATE = ( select max(L.JRN_DATE) from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> L where L.JRN_CONSUMED = '1' and L.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "L.[COL_NAME]\t= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "\n\t\t\t\tand\t", "", "PK")%> ) """ self.__ExecSql(self.requete)
# Create data view
self.requete = """ create view <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_WORK_SCHEMA")%>.<%=odiRef.getInfo( "JRN_DATA_VIEW")%> as select case when (<%=odiRef.getColList("", "convert(varchar<?=translator.translate(\u0022[SOURCE_DT]\u0022)?>,TARG.[COL_NAME])", " + ", "", "PK")%>) is null then 'D' else 'I' end <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_FLAG, JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN.JRN_DATE <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "JRN.[COL_NAME]\t\t" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "PK")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "TARG.[COL_NAME]\t\t" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "NOT PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN left outer join <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> TARG on ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "JRN.[COL_NAME]\t= TARG.[COL_NAME]", "\nand\t", "", "PK")%> ) where JRN.JRN_DATE = ( select max(L.JRN_DATE) from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> L where L.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "L.[COL_NAME]\t= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "\n\t\t\t\tand\t", "", "PK")%> ) """
self.__ExecSql(self.requete)
# Use Target Work Database self.repoCx.setCatalog(self.repodataschema)
# Create trigger UI self.requete = """ create trigger <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_WORK_SCHEMA")%>.<%=odiRef.getInfo( "JRN_UTRIGGER")%> on <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> for insert , update as insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "JRN_NAME", "A")%> ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_CONSUMED, JRN_FLAG, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> ) select sbs.JRN_SUBSCRIBER, '0', 'I', getdate(), <%=odiRef.getColList("", "ins.[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "SUBSCRIBER_TABLE", "A")%> sbs, inserted ins where sbs.JRN_TNAME= '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' """
self.__ExecSql(self.requete)
# Create trigger D
self.requete = """ create trigger <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_WORK_SCHEMA")%>.<%=odiRef.getInfo( "JRN_DTRIGGER")%> on <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> for delete as insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "JRN_NAME", "A")%> ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_CONSUMED, JRN_FLAG, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> ) select sbs.JRN_SUBSCRIBER, '0', 'D', getdate(), <%=odiRef.getColList("", "del.[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "SUBSCRIBER_TABLE", "A")%> sbs, deleted del where sbs.JRN_TNAME= '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' """ self.__ExecSql(self.requete)
self.repoCx.close()
def __ExecSql(self,sql): self.stmt.execute(sql) con = [ '<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_JAVA_DRIVER")%>' , '<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_JAVA_URL")%>' , '<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_USER_NAME")%>' , '<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_PASS")%>', '<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_WORK_CATALOG")%>', '<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_CATALOG")%>' ] JKM_MsSql=JMMMsSql(con)

prepDelStmt.close()

delCmd = """ delete from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> SUBS where SUBS.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = ? and SUBS.JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' """

insCmd = """ insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> ( JRN_TNAME, JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_REFDATE, JRN_ROW_COUNT, JRN_DATA_CMD, JRN_COUNT_CMD ) values ( /* JRN_TNAME */ '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>', /* JRN_SUBSCRIBER */ ?, /* JRN_REFDATE */ getdate(), /* JRN_ROW_COUNT */ 0, /* JRN_DATA_CMD */ null, /* JRN_COUNT_CMD */ 'update SUBS set SUBS.JRN_ROW_COUNT=(select count(''X'') from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN where JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER=''$$SUBSCRIBER_NAME$$'') from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> SUBS where SUBS.JRN_SUBSCRIBER=''$$SUBSCRIBER_NAME$$'' and SUBS.JRN_TNAME = ''<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>''' ) """
selCmd = """ select count('X') from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> SUBS where SUBS.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = ? and SUBS.JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' """
# Prepare the statements prepInsStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(insCmd) prepSelStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(selCmd)
# Execute for each subscriber for sbs in lstSbs: prepSelStmt.setString(1, sbs) rs = prepSelStmt.executeQuery() rs.next() nbSubs = rs.getInt(1) if (nbSubs == 0): prepInsStmt.setString(1, sbs) nbRows = prepInsStmt.executeUpdate()
prepInsStmt.close() prepSelStmt.close()
# Commit the updates myCon.commit()
